Program: Outlook
Title: 29/08/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00jpblq
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 30 Aug 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the experiences of Australian photo-journalist Nigel Brennan. He was kidnapped in Somalia along with a Canadian colleague Amanda Lindhout in 2008 and held hostage for 462 days. Meanwhile his family were desperately trying to raise a ransom of $3m. We hear from Nigel and his sister Nicky who negotiated with the kidnappers. Show less